    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a species of cud-chewing hoofed mammal of Africa, with long legs, a long neck, a coat pattern of irregular brown patches on a light background, and a prehensile tongue. There are nine subspecies of giraffes, classified on the basis of coat pattern and other minor physical differences.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
